## 🧑🏾‍🏫 what this challenge teaches u
super useful challenge to learn how cookies, browser protections, SameSite cookies, SOP work
in this challenge the crucial part was understanding SameSite
SameSite is a cookie attribute used to prevent CSRF. When SameSite=Lax (default) basically javascript executes and performs a cross site redirection, the cookies r not sent. the goal is to avoid data leakage.
but cookies r sent only in one situation: Top-Level GET navigation
to perform this we have 3 options:
-window.location
-Redirection 302 Found
-meta page refresh
this proves why javascript fetch function and <img src="..."> dont work in this case. cuz since they r NOT a Top-Level Navigation, cookies r not added to the request
also found out another way to run server: python3 -m http.server [PORT]

